message.entry: Trailing input arguments must occur in name-value pairs.
Changing ''ArrowSize'' value is not supported for undirected graphs.
Changing ''ArrowPosition'' value is not supported for undirected graphs.
Labels must be scalar, or a vector of length equal to the number of specified edges.
Graph does not contain node names.
''EdgeColor'' value must be a numeric RGB value or a color name.
''EdgeLabelColor'' value must be a numeric RGB value or a color name.

Setting edge colors is not available because the EdgeCData property was previously specified. Set the EdgeColor property of the GraphPlot object to a color to stop using EdgeCData, then reexecute the command that produced this error.

Unable to highlight edges because the EdgeColor property of the GraphPlot object is ''none''. To make only the highlighted edges in a GraphPlot object visible, set the EdgeColor property to a value other than ''none'', set the LineStyle property to ''none'', and then specify the LineStyle in the call to highlight.
G must have the same nodes and a subset of the edges of the plotted graph.
''NodeColor'' value must be a numeric RGB value or a color name.
''NodeLabelColor'' value must be a numeric RGB value or a color name.

Setting node colors is not available because the NodeCData property was previously specified. Set the NodeColor property of the GraphPlot object to a color to stop using NodeCData, then reexecute the command that produced this error.

Unable to highlight nodes because the NodeColor property of the GraphPlot object is ''none''. To make only the highlighted nodes in a GraphPlot object visible, set the NodeColor property to a value other than ''none'', set the Marker property to ''none'', and then specify the Marker in the call to highlight.
Unable to set ''EdgeColor'' value to ''none''. To make the highlighted edges invisible, specify ''LineStyle'' value as ''none''.
Unable to set ''NodeColor'' value to ''none''. To make the highlighted nodes invisible, specify ''Marker'' value as ''none''.
When using highlighting, specify a single ''LineStyle'' value of ''-'', ''--'', '':'', ''-.'', or ''none''.
'When using highlighting, specify a single ''Marker'' value of ''+'', ''o'', ''*'', ''.'', ''x'', ''square'', ''diamond'', ''v'', ''^'', ''>'', ''<'', ''pentagram'', ''hexagram'', or ''none''.

Specify nodes or edges to highlight.

Specify either node pairs or edges to highlight, but not both.
